Subject: [rest-discuss] auth now or later?


&gt; Suppose you have a URI like:
&gt;
&gt; /client/xyz
&gt;
&gt; where all paths beginning with &#39;client&#39; require authentication and &#39;xyz&#39;
&gt; could be any number of values.  When parsing the path, is it better to
check
&gt; authentication as soon as you encounter &#39;client&#39; or should you wait until
&gt; you have parsed the entire path and confirmed whether the path (and
&gt; therefore request URI) is valid or not?
&gt;
&gt; If you authenticate first, it would be possible to request authentication
&gt; for a URI that&#39;s not even valid.  On the other hand, authenticating only
&gt; valid URIs would possibly allow a malicious user to &quot;discover&quot; valid URIs
&gt; without being authenticated.
&gt;
&gt; Currently, I am implementing a system where I authenticate first, validate
&gt; the full path/URI second.  This greatly simplifies my code.  However, I am
&gt; curious to know if one approach is better than the other...
&gt;
&gt; Seairth
